Package com.im.njams.sdk.model

Class ProcessModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.im.njams.sdk.model.ProcessModel
  • public class ProcessModel
extends Object
    A ProcessModel represents one process/flow in engine to monitor. Instances of running jobs for the process are managed here.
    Author:
    pnientiedt

      • createJobWithExplicitLogId

        public Job createJobWithExplicitLogId​(String jobId,
                                      String logId)
        Don't use this method if you don't have to!
        Use either createJob() or createJob(String jobId).
        Creates a job with a given external jobId from Engine and with an explicitly set logId! This should only be used if you know what you are doing, because the logId normally is a UUID. E.g. this is a necessary method for the replay plugin, because it has to use the same logId as the job that is replayed.
        Parameters:
        jobId - the external jobId in Engine
        logId - the explicitly set logId
        Returns:
        the Job
